Fix it (pick ONE of the options below)
Option A — Update the chart and let it choose a valid tag
Shellhelm repo updatehelm upgrade --install kafka bitnami/kafka -n kafkaShow more lines
This refreshes the chart and pulls the current default tag that exists.

Option B — Explicitly pin a valid tag (simplest & reliable)
Use a tag that surely exists (Bitnami publishes major/minor aliases without the -rXX suffix). For Kafka 4.0.0:
Shellhelm upgrade --install kafka bitnami/kafka -n kafka \  --set image.tag=4.0.0Show more lines
If you also see an init container using the same repo, pin it too:
Shellhelm upgrade --install kafka bitnami/kafka -n kafka \  --set image.tag=4.0.0 \  --set controller.image.tag=4.0.0 \  --set defaultInitContainers.prepareConfig.image.tag=4.0.0Show more lines

After this, check:
Shellkubectl get pods -n kafkakubectl describe pod <one-of-the-pods> -n kafka | grep -i "image:"Show more lines


Option C — Pull from GitHub Container Registry (sometimes more up-to-date)
Bitnami mirrors images on GHCR. Point the chart to GHCR and pin a clean tag:
Shellhelm upgrade --install kafka bitnami/kafka -n kafka \  --set image.registry=ghcr.io \  --set image.repository=bitnami/kafka \  --set image.tag=4.0.0Show more lines

If you still hit ImagePullBackOff after pinning


Verify the exact tag in use
Shellkubectl describe pod <pod> -n kafka | grep -i "image:"Show more lines
Ensure it matches what you set.


Minikube docker-env (if you’re building locally)
If you built a local image, ensure you built it inside Minikube’s Docker:
Shelleval $(minikube docker-env)docker pull docker.io/bitnami/kafka:4.0.0Show more lines


Rate limits / transient errors
Try once more or switch to GHCR as in Option C.



Why did this happen?

The chart revision you installed referenced bitnami/kafka:4.0.0-debian-12-r10.
That exact digest/tag is missing in Docker Hub now (Bitnami periodically retires or replaces -rXX sub-tags).
Pinning to 4.0.0 (without -rXX) or updating the chart removes the mismatch.
